The paper discusses risk-limiting audits for elections, which involves statistical analysis and probability calculations. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with ensuring the accuracy and integrity of election results. The paper also discusses approaches to ballot-polling and comparison audits, which involve data analysis and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), cybernetics (cs.CY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
